.\" shlib - A shell library of reusable functions
.TH SHLIB 7 "January 2026" "shlib 0.1.0" "Shell Library"
.SH NAME
shlib \- a shell library of reusable Bash functions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B source
.I /path/to/shlib/lib/shlib.sh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shlib
is a library of reusable Bash functions that can be sourced into shell scripts.
It provides common utilities for logging, command checking, and other frequently
needed operations.
.PP
The library enables strict mode
.RB ( "set \-euo pipefail" )
when sourced. It includes double-source protection to prevent loading multiple times.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.SS Core
.TP
.B shlib::version
Print the library version to stdout.
.TP
.BI shlib::command_exists " command"
Check if
.I command
exists in PATH. Returns 0 if found, 1 otherwise.
.SS Logging
.TP
.BI shlib::header " message"
Print
.I message
to stdout in bold (without trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::headern " message"
Print
.I message
to stdout in bold (with trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::error " message"
Print
.I message
to stderr with "error:" prefix (without trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::errorn " message"
Print
.I message
to stderr with "error:" prefix (with trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::warn " message"
Print
.I message
to stdout with "warning:" prefix (without trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::warnn " message"
Print
.I message
to stdout with "warning:" prefix (with trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::info " message"
Print
.I message
to stdout with "info:" prefix (without trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::infon " message"
Print
.I message
to stdout with "info:" prefix (with trailing newline).
.SS Colorized Logging
.TP
.BI shlib::cerror " message"
Print
.I message
to stderr with red "error:" prefix (without trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::cerrorn " message"
Print
.I message
to stderr with red "error:" prefix (with trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::cwarn " message"
Print
.I message
to stdout with yellow "warning:" prefix (without trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::cwarnn " message"
Print
.I message
to stdout with yellow "warning:" prefix (with trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::cinfo " message"
Print
.I message
to stdout with blue "info:" prefix (without trailing newline).
.TP
.BI shlib::cinfon " message"
Print
.I message
to stdout with blue "info:" prefix (with trailing newline).
.SH VARIABLES
.TP
.B SHLIB_VERSION
The library version string (readonly).
.TP
.B SHLIB_DIR
Absolute path to the directory containing shlib.sh (readonly).
.TP
.B SHLIB_LOADED
Set to 1 when library is loaded. Used for double-source protection (readonly).
.TP
.B SHLIB_COLOR_RED
ANSI escape code for red color (readonly).
.TP
.B SHLIB_COLOR_YELLOW
ANSI escape code for yellow color (readonly).
.TP
.B SHLIB_COLOR_BLUE
ANSI escape code for blue color (readonly).
.TP
.B SHLIB_COLOR_RESET
ANSI escape code to reset color (readonly).
.TP
.B SHLIB_COLOR_BOLD
ANSI escape code for bold text (readonly).
.SH EXAMPLES
Basic usage in a script:
.PP
.RS
.nf
#!/usr/bin/env bash
source /path/to/shlib/lib/shlib.sh

shlib::headern "Starting script..."

if shlib::command_exists git; then
    shlib::cinfon "git is available"
else
    shlib::cerrorn "git is required"
    exit 1
fi
.fi
.RE
.PP
Check the library version:
.PP
.RS
.nf
source /path/to/shlib/lib/shlib.sh
echo "Using shlib version $(shlib::version)"
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I lib/shlib.sh
The library file to source.
.TP
.I tests/*.bats
Test files using the Bats testing framework.
.TP
.I examples/basic_usage.sh
Example script demonstrating library usage.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Functions that check conditions return 0 on success and 1 on failure.
Logging functions always return 0.
